Cook the rice according to the package directions. Warm the oil in a Dutch oven set over medium heat. Add the onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic, file powder, paprika, thyme, and salt. Cook, stirring often, for 5 to 7 minutes, or until the vegetables are soft. Add the broth, chicken, tomato sauce, and 1 cup (250 mL) water. Stir to mix. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes to blend the flavors. To serve, spoon the gumbo into shallow bowls. Top with a dollop of rice.